SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c01603910
Version: 1

HPSBMA02385 SSRT080161 rev.1 - HP Service Manager (HPSM), Gain Extended Privileges

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2008-11-12
Last Updated: 2008-11-12

Potential Security Impact: Gain extended privileges

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP Service Manager v7.01. The vulnerability could be exploited to gain extended privileges.

References: CVE-2008-4415

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Service Manager (HPSM) prior to v7.01.71 running on AIX, HP-UX, Linux, Solaris, and Windows

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics 
===============================================
Reference                         Base Vector               Base Score 
CVE-2008-4415     (AV:N/AC:L/Au:S/C:C/I:C/A:C)      9.0
===============================================
Information on CVSS is documented in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002.

RESOLUTION

HP has made patches available to resolve the vulnerabilities.

The patches are available from http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/patches 

Operating System - AIX
Patch - HPSM_00019 or subsequent
 
Operating System - HP-UX (IA)
Patch - HPSM_00020 or subsequent
 
Operating System - HP-UX (PA)
Patch - HPSM_00021 or subsequent
 
Operating System - Linux
Patch - HPSM_00022 or subsequent
 
Operating System - Solaris
Patch - HPSM_00023 or subsequent
 
Operating System - Windows
Patch - HPSM_00024 or subsequent


MANUAL ACTIONS: Yes - NonUpdate 
Apply the appropriate patch as described in the Resolution. 

PRODUCT SPECIFIC INFORMATION 

HP-UX Software Assistant: HP-UX Software Assistant is an enhanced application that replaces HP-UX Security Patch Check. It analyzes all Security Bulletins issued by HP and lists recommended actions that may apply to a specific HP-UX system. It can also download patches and create a depot automatically. For more information see https://www.hp.com/go/swa 

The following text is for use by the HP-UX Software Assistant.

AFFECTED VERSIONS (for HP-UX)

HP-UX B.11.23 (IA) 
============= 
For HP Service Manager 7.01 
action: install HPSM_00020 if running Service Manager 
URL: http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/patches 

HP-UX B.11.23 (PA) 
HP-UX B.11.11 
============= 
For HP Service Manager 7.01 
action: install HPSM_00021 if running Service Manager 
URL: http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/patches 

END AFFECTED VERSIONS (for HP-UX)

